.TH COLT 1 "April 2026" "colt" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
colt \- a vi-style modal terminal text editor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B colt
.RI [ filename ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B colt
is a modal terminal text editor written in Pony. It uses vi/vim-style
keybindings with modal editing (Normal, Insert, Visual, Command, Search).
.PP
When started with a filename, colt loads the file into the buffer.
Without a filename, it opens an empty buffer.
.SH MODES
.TP
.B Normal
Default mode for navigation and commands. Press
.B Escape
from Insert mode to return here.
.TP
.B Insert
Text entry mode. Enter with
.BR i ,
.BR a ,
.BR o ,
.B I ,
.BR A ,
.BR O .
Exit with
.BR Escape .
.TP
.B Command
Ex-style command entry. Enter with
.BR : .
.TP
.B Search
Search entry. Enter with
.B /
or
.BR ? .
.TP
.B Visual
Character-wise visual selection. Enter with
.BR v .
.TP
.B Visual Line
Line-wise visual selection. Enter with
.BR V .
.SH KEY BINDINGS
.SS Normal Mode
.TP
.B h / j / k / l
Move cursor left / down / up / right
.TP
.B w / b / e
Word forward / word backward / word end
.TP
.B 0 / ^ / $
Line start / first non-blank / line end
.TP
.B gg / G / {n}G
File start / file end / line number
.TP
.B f / F / t / T
Find character on line (forward/backward, to/at)
.TP
.B ; / ,
Repeat last find (same/reverse direction)
.TP
.B i / I / a / A / o / O
Enter Insert mode (various positions)
.TP
.B d{motion}
Delete (motion form, e.g.
.BR dd ,
.BR dw ,
.B d$ )
.TP
.B y{motion}
Yank (e.g.
.BR yy ,
.BR yw )
.TP
.B c{motion}
Change (delete and enter Insert)
.TP
.B p / P
Paste after / before cursor
.TP
.B u / Ctrl-R
Undo / Redo
.TP
.B %
Jump to matching bracket
.TP
.B Ctrl-A / Ctrl-X
Increment / decrement number
.TP
.B ~
Toggle case
.TP
.B > / <
Indent / dedent
.TP
.B "a-{letter}
Select register for next operation
.SS Text Objects
.TP
.B diw
Delete inner word
.TP
.B ci"
Change inside quotes
.TP
.B da(
Delete around parentheses
.TP
.B yi{
Yank inside braces
.SS Visual Mode
.TP
.B v
Toggle character-wise visual
.TP
.B V
Toggle line-wise visual
.TP
.B d / y / c
Delete / yank / change selection
.SS Command Mode
.TP
.B :w
Save
.TP
.B :q / :q!
Quit / force quit
.TP
.B :wq / :x
Save and quit
.TP
.B :e {file}
Open file
.TP
.B :s/pat/rep/[g]
Substitute (literal string, g for global)
.TP
.B :%s/pat/rep/[g]
Substitute across all lines
.TP
.B :{n}
Go to line number
.TP
.B :set relativenumber
Toggle relative line numbers
.TP
.B :set tabstop={n}
Set tab width
.TP
.B :help
Show help screen
.SS Registers
.TP
.B "0
Last yanked text (auto)
.TP
.B "1-"9
Last 9 deletions (auto-shift)
.TP
.B "a-"z
Named registers
.TP
.B "+
System clipboard (via xclip/pbcopy)
.SH FILES
.TP
.B /tmp/colt_clipboard
Temporary file used for clipboard operations.
.SH NOTES
On Linux, clipboard integration requires one of:
.BR wl-clipboard ,
.BR xclip ,
or
.B xsel
installed. The editor tries each in order and falls back silently if none
are available. On macOS,
.B pbcopy
and
.B pbpaste
are used (included by default).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
No special environment variables are used.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR vim (1)
